1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,357
[INTRO]

2
00:00:00,657 --> 00:00:02,085
You open the laptop.

3
00:00:02,385 --> 00:00:03,457
The screen glows.

4
00:00:03,757 --> 00:00:05,185
Pure logic. Clean. Instant.

5
00:00:05,485 --> 00:00:07,628
You write five lines of code.

6
00:00:07,928 --> 00:00:10,428
It works perfectly on the first try.

7
00:00:10,728 --> 00:00:12,514
You feel like a wizard.

8
00:00:12,814 --> 00:00:16,385
Then you close the laptop and reach for the iron.

9
00:00:16,685 --> 00:00:17,757
The spell breaks.

10
00:00:18,057 --> 00:00:18,414
[HOOK]

11
00:00:18,714 --> 00:00:22,285
Everyone thinks you hate soldering because you burn your thumb.

12
00:00:22,585 --> 00:00:24,371
Or the joint is cold.

13
00:00:24,671 --> 00:00:26,099
Or the pad lifts.

14
00:00:26,399 --> 00:00:26,757
No.

15
00:00:27,057 --> 00:00:28,485
You hate it existentially.

16
00:00:28,785 --> 00:00:31,642
Code exists in a Platonic realm of ideas.

17
00:00:31,942 --> 00:00:35,157
Soldering is a negotiation with raw, sweating, awkward physics.

18
00:00:35,457 --> 00:00:38,671
It reminds you that making is not just thinking.

19
00:00:38,971 --> 00:00:40,399
It is a fight.

20
00:00:40,699 --> 00:00:41,057
[BODY]

21
00:00:41,357 --> 00:00:44,214
That fight is the source of the hate.

22
00:00:44,514 --> 00:00:48,442
In software, every mistake is a thought you can take back.

23
00:00:48,742 --> 00:00:49,814
Ctrl+Z. Instant grace.

24
00:00:50,114 --> 00:00:52,971
In hardware, the solder wicks where it wants.

25
00:00:53,271 --> 00:00:54,342
The flux spits.

26
00:00:54,642 --> 00:00:55,714
The joint solidifies.

27
00:00:56,014 --> 00:00:59,585
You look at it and know: this is permanent now.

28
00:00:59,885 --> 00:01:01,671
That permanence is the anxiety.

29
00:01:01,971 --> 00:01:07,685
The fear of the irreversible is what you actually smell when the smoke hits the air.

30
00:01:07,985 --> 00:01:08,342
[EXAMPLE]

31
00:01:08,642 --> 00:01:10,428
I built a split keyboard.

32
00:01:10,728 --> 00:01:12,871
The layout code was a symphony.

33
00:01:13,171 --> 00:01:14,600
Perfect layers. Perfect combos.

34
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:17,042
The PCBs arrived. Thin. Green. Fragile.

